  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou2-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/fda-cdrh-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All ten assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels at MRL 5. Output comparison (E_rms = 9.3%) and discretization error (GCI < 2%) provide the strongest quantitative evidence of model fidelity. Monte Carlo UQ on 1000 samples confirms that input and model-form uncertainties do not materially alter the conclusion that predicted NIH values remain below the clinical acceptance threshold across all five COU operating points. The three scoped-out factors (Use error, Test samples, Equivalency of input parameters) are each supported by documented justifications that bound the scope of the scoping decision and impose re-activation triggers for future COU revisions. No weakeners are identified. The credibility body of evidence is sufficient to accept the CFD model for predicting absolute hemolysis levels in the Class III VAD COU.",
